This paper deals with the security of in-vehicle networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, specifically long short term memory (LSTM) neural networks, for anomaly detection, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the development of a software-defined network, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the communication requirements of the in-vehicle network, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
